```

The indexing half and the segment sync half are connected only through the SQS commit queue. Both halves run as concurrent ZIO fibers within the same process. If the segment sync fiber fails and restarts, in-flight commit events remain in SQS and will be reprocessed. If the writer process itself crashes after a commit but before publishing, the commit event is lost â€” this is an acceptable tradeoff given that Lucene commits are durable and the next commit will upload all outstanding segments anyway.

